  "name": "Ring of Magic (Apex)",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This ring is made from the purest platinum and is covered in esoteric magical symbols. It does nothing unless you have a spellcasting class feature. While wearing the ring of magic, you gain a +2 item bonus to the skill corresponding to one of your spellcasting traditions, and have two additional 6th-rank and one additional 5rd-rank spell slots each day. You prepare spells in these slots or cast from them spontaneously, just as you normally cast your spells. When you invest the ring, you either increase your spellcasting attribute modifier by 1, or increase it to +4, whichever would give you a higher value.</p><p>If you take off the ring for any reason, you lose the additional spell slots. You can't gain spell slots from more than one ring of magic per day, nor can a single ring of magic grant spell slots more than once per day.</p><p>If you can cast spells in a variety of different ways (such as if you are a draconic bloodline sorcerer with the wizard multiclass archetype), you can divide the spell slots as you wish among your various sources of spells.</p><hr /><p><strong>Activate - </strong><span class=\"action-glyph\">1</span> (concentrate)</p><p><strong>Frequency </strong>once per day</p><p><strong>Effect</strong> You regain one expended spell slot that must be of a lower rank than the highest rank spell you can cast.</p><hr /><p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> You have a spellcasting class feature.</p>"
    },
